Title : Meridian Dan
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}
{{Use British English|date=January 2015}}
'''Meridian Dan''' (born '''Daniel Lawrence London''')<ref name="youtube">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jQ_FOa5uOig&safe=active |title=Meridian Dan - Interview: Talks New Album 'I Am London' & More |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref> is a [[Grime (music)|grime]] MC from [[Tottenham]], North London.<ref name="tottenham">{{cite web|author=Comment * |url=http://www.contactmusic.com/press/meridian-dan-signs-to-pmr-records-german-whip-to-get-official-release-on-31st-march-2014 |title=Meridian Dan Signs To Pmr Records 'German Whip' To Get Official Release On 31st March 2014 |publisher=Contactmusic.com |date=2014-03-31 |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref> He is best known for his 2014 single "[[German Whip]]", and is a former member of seminal grime crews Meridian and Bloodline.

==Background==
Lawrence first started MCing at age 10, having had music around him throughout his childhood and being inspired by hip-hop and reggae.<ref name="fabriclondon"/> [[Jme (MC)|Jme]] and Big H, who both feature on "German Whip", were both childhood friends.<ref name="fabriclondon"/>

Meridian Dan was a peripheral member of [[Meridian Crew]] along with President T, Skepta, Jme, [[Big H (rapper)|Big H]], Bossman Birdie and Paper Pabs in the early noughties. During his time in the group he made regular appearances on the crew's show on pirate radio station Heat FM show and later on Déjà Vu FM.<ref name="fabriclondon"/> He featured on Skepta's "Private Caller" single in 2005.<ref name="allmusic">{{cite web|author=Artist Biography by Aneet Nijjar |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/meridian-dan-mn0003219391/biography |title=Meridian Dan &#124; Biography |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref> In 2005, Meridian Dan took a hiatus from music after Meridian Crew disbanded - with other crew members going on to form [[Boy Better Know]] and Bloodline Family - to pursue other interests and careers. During this time, he worked as a boxer,<ref name="allmusic"/> a steward at [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], a plasterer, an electrician, a steel erector, and a welder.<ref name="ds">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a564717/german-whip-is-climbing-the-chart-but-who-is-meridian-dan.html#~oEOiuzfRtAkkdV#ixzz32GR8zZHb |title='German Whip' is climbing the chart, but who is Meridian Dan? |publisher=Digital Spy |date=2014-04-15 |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref> In a 2014 interview, Meridian Dan said that his hiatus was because he wasn't getting paid for his music and had outside stresses to attend to.<ref name="fabriclondon">{{cite web|author="I am nothing but a grime MC": Introducing Meridian Dan |url=http://www.fabriclondon.com/blog/view/i-am-nothing-but-a-grime-mc-introducing-meridian-dan |title="I am nothing but a grime MC": Introducing Meridian Dan|work=fabric blog |publisher=Fabriclondon.com |date=2014-04-14 |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref>

He returned to making music in 2010 recording songs and making pirate radio appearances with other members of Bloodline Family.<ref name="allmusic"/> In 2013 he recorded [[German Whip]] featuring [[Big H (rapper)|Big H]] of Bloodline and [[Jme (MC)|Jme]] of Boy Better Know, after the song achieved underground success Meridian Dan was signed to [[PMR Records|PMR]] who gave the song a commercial release in 2014. German Whip charted at #13 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name="officialcharts">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/meridian%20dan%20featuring%20big%20h%20%26%20jme/ |title=Meridian Dan Featuring Big H & Jme &#124; Artist |publisher=Official Charts |date= |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref> This led the [[London Evening Standard]] to quip that his jump to stardom must have been "one of the slowest breakthroughs in music".<ref name="les">{{cite web|author=David Smyth |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/goingout/music/virtually-famous-meridian-dan-9126755.html |title=Virtually famous: Meridian Dan|work=London Evening Standard |date=2014-02-14 |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref>

==Music==
In August 2014 the song One Two Drinks was announced as the next single from his forthcoming debut album ''I Am London'' which is set to be released on PMR. In summer 2015 he also released single 'The Bits' which was also released under PMR.<ref>http://grmdaily.com/meridian-dan-drops-another-banger-one-two-drinks</ref><ref name="factmag">{{cite web|url=http://www.factmag.com/2014/01/22/meridian-dan-signs-album-deal-with-pmr-german-whip-to-see-full-release-on-march-31/|title=Meridian Dan signs album deal with PMR: 'German Whip' to see full release on March 31|work=FACT Magazine |date=2014-01-22 |accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref>

==Awards==
In September 2014 Meridian Dan received three nominations for awards in '''Mobo Best Grime, Best Song and Best Newcomer'''<ref>http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a598544/mobo-awards-2014-nominations-in-full. |  Meridian Dan nominated for Mobo awards |Digital Spy |Retrieved 2014-10-01</ref>

